Poland Rejects Mite-Infested Rapeseed From Ukraine and Moldova

-- B y   R u d y   R u i t e n b e r g
-- 
2011-10-11T11:22:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-11/poland-rejects-mite-infested-rapeseed-from-ukraine-and-moldova.html
Poland  rejected rapeseed cargoes
from  Ukraine  and Moldova because of infestation with live and
dead mites, notifications to the European Unionâ€™s food-alert
system showed.  Five samples of rapeseed from Ukraine tested from Oct. 7 to
Oct. 9 found between 20 and 100 mites a kilogram (2.2 pounds),
according to  notices  from Poland. Two samples of cargoes from
Moldova on Oct. 8-9 found 300 and 210 of the insects a kilogram,
respectively, notices showed.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rudy Ruitenberg in Paris at 
 rruitenberg@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
